Tools to use:
✅ Multi-provider fallback
✅ Semantic caching
✅ Model downscaling
✅ Prompt condensation
✅ RAG for stadium knowledge
✅ Mock/demo data for risky real-time features
✅ Vercel/Firebase free hosting

Main AI stack
Primary: Gemini Flash
Backup: Groq Llama 3.3 / Llama 3.1
Optional final fallback: static cached answer

AI architecture:
React App
  ↓
AI Service Layer
  ↓
1. Check semantic cache
  ↓
2. If no cached answer, classify task
  ↓
3. Use cheapest/smallest model first
  ↓
4. If quota/rate error, fallback to next provider
  ↓
5. Save answer to cache
  ↓
Return answer to user

Gemini Flash:
- multilingual fan Q&A
- route explanation
- simple translation
- alert rewriting
- accessibility guidance

Groq:
- backup chat response
- fast summary
- incident summarization
- volunteer/staff assistant

Gemini Pro / stronger model:
- only for complex operational reasoning
- not for every user chat

Implementaion:
Firestore collection: aiCache

Fields:
- normalizedQuestion
- answer
- category
- language
- stadiumId
- createdAt
- usageCount

Quota safe:
Normal navigation → database answer
Repeated question → cache
Translation → Gemini Flash
Staff incident summary → Groq/Gemini
Complex decision support → Gemini stronger model

| Need                           | Tool                                                                  | Why                                                                                                                 |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1. Login / logout              | **Firebase Auth**                                                     | Google login, email login, role-based users                                                                         |
| 2. Save data                   | **Cloud Firestore**                                                   | Stores users, incidents, routes, alerts, cache                                                                      |
| 3. App data sync               | **Firestore realtime listeners**                                      | Fan/staff dashboards update live                                                                                    |
| 4. Give info                   | **Firestore + AI service layer**                                      | Static info from DB, AI only when needed                                                                            |
| 5. Multilingual help           | **Gemini Flash + cached translations**                                | Main multilingual assistant                                                                                         |
| 6. Info and updates            | **Firestore alerts collection**                                       | Staff creates update → fans see it live                                                                             |
| 7. Basic app needs             | **React + Firebase + Gemini + Groq fallback**                         | Enough for MVP without complex cloud setup                                                                          |
| 8. Staff language → fan alerts | **Gemini translation + Firestore alert object**                       | Staff reports in Telugu/Hindi/etc., fans receive in chosen language                                                 |
| 9. Location/maps               | **Google Maps API if billing okay; fallback Leaflet + OpenStreetMap** | Google Maps needs billing-enabled project/API key; OSM/Leaflet is safer free fallback. ([Google for Developers][1]) |
| 10. Notifications              | **In-app Firestore notifications first; FCM optional**                | In-app is safer. Push notifications can be added later                                                              |
| 11. Speech/text/size           | **Web Speech API + accessibility settings**                           | Browser speech synthesis/recognition; recognition has limited browser support. ([MDN Web Docs][2])                  |
| 12. Updating route             | **Route engine using stadium graph + crowd data**                     | Recalculate safest/least crowded route from Firestore updates                                                       |

